  "prompt": "Why does WiFi turn on in airplane mode?",
  "response": "WiFi doesn't turn on by default in airplane mode. When you enable airplane mode, all wireless communication (cellular, WiFi, Bluetooth) is typically disabled. However, on many modern devices, you can manually re-enable WiFi while still keeping airplane mode active. This allows you to use WiFi on an airplane when permitted by the airline and flight crew. To do this, you would need to:\n\n1. First enable airplane mode\n2. Then separately turn on WiFi in your device's settings\n\nThis feature gives users more flexibility while still primarily disabling cellular communications during flights.",
